divs: Sighting DetailsI had just left the courthouse and came home to let my dog out for a bit and went out to play fetch with him and smoke a cigarette. I noticed all of a sudden what I thought was a shooting star so I paused, but it didn't burn out it kept going and it was moving fast, too fast to be a satellite. So I grabbed my camera and started recording I didn't think I would end up catching anything, but I provided the extracted part that is zoomed in and slowed it down. I also have the original which is about 3 minutes long, but not all of it captures the object. However the original video does have reference points such as my roof and I think trees as well before I zoom in. I would like to know what this is, because I have never seen a shape like this.
Object Shape: Bullet, Missile, Cigar, Cylinder, Sphere, Star-like, Teardrop
Summary: Thought I saw a shooting start but it was lasting too long so I started recording
